tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id UUID NOT NULL,
  sensor_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  value FLOAT NOT NULL,
  timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE WearableDevices (
    device_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    device_type TEXT,
    sensor_type TEXT,
    sensor_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE ResearchParticipants (
    participant_id VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
    age INTEGER,
    gender TEXT,
    height FLOAT,
    weight FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE WearableDevices (
  device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name VARCHAR(50),
  sensor_type VARCHAR(20),
  sensor_data FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE ResearchSubjects (
  subject_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  subject_name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  condition VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE SensorDataArchive (
  data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id INT,
  sensor_type VARCHAR(20),
  sensor_data FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (device_id) REFERENCES WearableDevices(device_id)
);

CREATE TABLE participant (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    study_id INT,
    device_id INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    age INT
);

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    device_id INT,
    sensor_type VARCHAR(50),
    sensor_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
